  "response": "Here are some lesser-known but interesting places to visit in Pune:\n\n1. Historical and Cultural Sites\n\u2022 Shaniwar Wada Palace\n\u2022 Vishrambaug Wada\n\u2022 Pataleshwar Cave Temple\n\u2022 Raja Dinkar Kelkar Museum\n\n2. Natural and Scenic Locations\n\u2022 Sinhagad Fort\n\u2022 Mulshi Dam\n\u2022 Panshet Dam\n\u2022 Tamhini Ghat\n\u2022 Lavasa Hill Station\n\n3. Offbeat Attractions\n\u2022 Tribal Museum\n\u2022 Katraj Snake Park\n\u2022 National Defence Academy Museum\n\u2022 Osho Ashram\n\u2022 Saras Baug\n\u2022 Chaturshringi Temple\n\n4. Weekend Getaways Near Pune\n\u2022 Lonavala\n\u2022 Mahabaleshwar\n\u2022 Matheran\n\u2022 Khandala\n\n5. Unique Experiences\n\u2022 Dagdusheth Halwai Ganpati Temple\n\u2022 Pune Okayama Friendship Garden\n\u2022 Empress Garden\n\u2022 Agakhan Palace\n\nThese places offer a mix of history, culture, nature, and unique experiences that are often overlooked by typical tourists. Each location provides a different perspective on Pune's rich heritage and diverse landscape.",
